    int n = sizeof(nums) / sizeof(nums[0]);

    quicksort(nums, 0, n - 1);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cout << nums[i] << " ";
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This implements the quicksort algorithm. The partition function takes the last element as pivot, partitions the array, and returns the pivot index. The quicksort function then recursively calls itself to sort the left and right parts of the pivot.

The time complexity is O(nlog(n)) since we are dividing the problem in half on each recursive call. The space complexity is O(log(n)) due to recursion stack.

