3) Expand the squared term and distribute the negative sign: \begin{align*} x^2 - 2x\\sqrt{11-2x} + 11 - 2x &= 16\\end{align*}  
4) Group like terms: \begin{align*} x^2 - 2x + 11 - 2x\\sqrt{11-2x} &= 16\\end{align*}
5) Subtract 11 from both sides: \begin{align*} x^2 - 4x - 2x\\sqrt{11-2x} &= 5\\end{align*}  
6) Factorize the quadratic: \begin{align*} (x-5)(x+1) - 2x\\sqrt{11-2x} &= 5\\end{align*}  
7) Divide both sides by $(x-5)(x+1)$: \begin{align*} \\frac{-2x\\sqrt{11-2x}}{(x-5)(x+1)} &= \\frac{5}{(x-5)(x+1)}\\end{align*}  
8) Take the square root of both sides: \begin{align*} -\\sqrt{\\frac{11-2x}{x-5}} &= \\pm \\sqrt{5}\\end{align*}
9) Substitute $y = \\sqrt{11-2x}$: \begin{align*} y &= \\pm \\sqrt{5}\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{x-5}}\\end{align*}
